import java.util.LinkedHashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class FirstNonRepeatingChar {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String input = "automation";
        Map<Character, Integer> map = new LinkedHashMap<>();

        // Step 1: Count characters
        for (char ch : input.toCharArray()) {
            map.put(ch, map.getOrDefault(ch, 0) + 1);
        }

        // Step 2: Find first non-repeating character
        for (Map.Entry<Character, Integer> entry : map.entrySet()) {
            if (entry.getValue() == 1) {
                System.out.println(entry.getKey());
                break;
            }
        }
    }
}

Why this works (Interview Explanation)

LinkedHashMap â†’ insertion order maintain

First loop â†’ frequency count

Second loop â†’ first value == 1 milte hi break

Efficient & readable


Complexity

Time: O(n)

Space: O(n)

---
Why not use HashMap?

ğŸ‘‰ Order guarantee nahi, isliye â€œfirstâ€ non-repeating galat ho sakta hai.

