Yes (Array approach):
int[] freq = new int[256];

for (char ch : input.toCharArray()) {
    freq[ch]++;
}

for (char ch : input.toCharArray()) {
    if (freq[ch] == 1) {
        System.out.println(ch);
        break;
    }
}
What if no non-repeating character exists?
Handle with flag / Optional
System.out.println("No unique character found");

